    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-05-23T08:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-05-23T08:00:00-05:00" n="364"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d364">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">835.731/51: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Armour</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Buenos Aires</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-05-23T10:00:00-03:00"
                            >May 23, 1944—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 11:20 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1301. Embassy’s 1299 of May 22, midnight.<note n="80" xml:id="d364fn80">Not
                        printed.</note> Following informal notification of suspension of All
                    America’s closure Post Office resolution issued early this morning modifies
                    previous resolution reported in Embassy’s 1296, of May 22<note n="80"
                        xml:id="d364fn81">Not printed.</note> to provide for strict warning to the
                    company but no other action. It is understood that issuance <pb facs="0420"
                        n="406" xml:id="pg_406"/> of second resolution followed bitter quarrel
                    within Ministry of Interior and belated realization that international
                    complications, especially as regards Mexico, might result.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Armour</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
